The paper is organised as follows. A brief description of the ATLAS detector is given in Sect. 2. The signal and background Monte Carlo (MC) simulation samples used are described in Sect. 3. The reconstruction of physics objects is explained in Sect. 4, and the event selection is described in Sect. 5. Estimation of the SM backgrounds is outlined in Sect. 6. The results are described in Sect. 7 and the systematic uncertainties are given in Sect. 8. The interpretation of results in terms of models of pair production of dark-matter candidates and of BSM production of a high-mass Zγ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
